n = int(input())
points = []
for _ in range(4 * n + 1):
    x, y = map(int, input().split())
    points.append((x, y))

for i in range(len(points)):
    candidate = points[i]
    others = points[:i] + points[i+1:]
    xs = [x for x, y in others]
    ys = [y for x, y in others]
    min_x, max_x = min(xs), max(xs)
    min_y, max_y = min(ys), max(ys)
    valid = True
    for (x, y) in others:
        if not (x == min_x or x == max_x or y == min_y or y == max_y):
            valid = False
            break
    if not valid:
        continue
    left = sum(1 for (x, y) in others if x == min_x)
    right = sum(1 for (x, y) in others if x == max_x)
    bottom = sum(1 for (x, y) in others if y == min_y)
    top = sum(1 for (x, y) in others if y == max_y)
    if left >= n and right >= n and bottom >= n and top >= n:
        print(candidate[0], candidate[1])
        exit()
